subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is very similar to
H. divisus
(Wollaston, 1858), but differs from the later by having the temple shorter, transverse diameter of eye 1.5 x longer than temple (longer, 1.2 x longer than temple in
H. divisus
), malar space 0.75 x height of eye (0.55 x in
H. divisus
), mesosoma length 2.0 x maximum height (1.7 x in
H. divisus
), prescutellar depression with single high median carina (with three carinae in
H. divisus
), pterostigma narrow, 4.2 x longer than wide (wide, 2.8 x longer than wide in
H. divisus
), radial vein (r) of fore wing arising from middle of pterostigma (distinctly before in
H. divisus
), recurrent vein (m-cu) weakly antefurcal (distinctly postfurcal in
H. divisus
), hind femur narrow, 4.3 x longer than wide (wide, 3.6 x longer than wide in
H. divisus
), vertex and frons entirely smooth (finely and densely striate in
H. divisus
), mesoscutum finely to very finely coriaceous (distinctly granulate in
H. divisus
) and distribution in Korean Peninsula (in the south of the Western Palaearctic in
H. divisus
).
